Desert Ecology

For this assignment, we are going to use a modified data set on desert ecology. The data are from: S. K. Morgan Ernest, Thomas J. Valone, and James H. Brown. 2009. Long-term monitoring and experimental manipulation of a Chihuahuan Desert ecosystem near Portal, Arizona, USA. Ecology 90:1708.

  1. What is the proportion of taxa included in this study? Show a table and plot that reflects this count.
deserts %>% 
  count(taxa)
## # A tibble: 4 x 2
##   taxa        n
## * <chr>   <int>
## 1 Bird      450
## 2 Rabbit     75
## 3 Reptile    14
## 4 Rodent  34247
deserts %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = taxa))+
  geom_bar()+
  coord_flip()+
  labs(title="Taxa in the Chihuahuan Desert", x="Taxa", y="Count")+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 10))

  1. Add another layer to your answer from #4 using geom_point to get an idea of how many measurements were taken for each species.
deserts %>%

  1. What is the relationship between weight and hindfoot length? Consider whether or not over plotting is an issue.
deserts %>% 
  filter(weight!="NA") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=weight, y=hindfoot_length))+
  geom_point(size=0.25, na.rm=T)+
  labs(title="Weight vs. Hindfoot Length", x="Weight", y="Hindfoot Length")+
  geom_smooth(method=lm, se=T, na.rm=T)+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 10))

  1. Which two species have, on average, the highest weight? Once you have identified them, make a new column that is a ratio of weight to hindfoot_length. Make a plot that shows the range of this new ratio and fill by sex.
deserts %>% 
  filter(weight!="NA") %>% 
  group_by(species) %>% 
  summarise(avg_weight=mean(weight, na.rm=T)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(avg_weight))

deserts %>% 
  filter(weight!="NA") %>%
  mutate(weight_to_hindfoot_length_ratio=weight/hindfoot_length) %>%
  group_by(species) %>% 
  select(species, weight_to_hindfoot_length_ratio) %>% 
  arrange(desc(weight_to_hindfoot_length_ratio))
## # A tibble: 32,283 x 2

deserts %>% 
  filter(weight!="NA", sex!="NA")%>%
  mutate(weight_to_hindfoot_length_ratio=weight/hindfoot_length) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=species, y=weight_to_hindfoot_length_ratio, fill=sex))+
  geom_boxplot(size=0.75, na.rm=T)+
  labs(title="Ratio of Weight to Hindfoot Length by Sex", x="Species", y="Weight to Hindfoot Length Ratio")+
  coord_flip()+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 10))
